1
00:00:19,033 --> 00:00:22,367
Grandma, you remember Celeste
in everything we cook.

2
00:00:22,433 --> 00:00:26,867
Yes, of course, somehow
my memory is still sharp.

3
00:00:26,933 --> 00:00:30,267
Until now I know how much
you love Celeste.

4
00:00:30,333 --> 00:00:31,833
That was before...

5
00:00:31,900 --> 00:00:33,467
but not anymore.

6
00:00:33,533 --> 00:00:35,333
Love, thank you so much
for saving me

7
00:00:35,433 --> 00:00:37,767
from this horrible situation.

8
00:00:37,833 --> 00:00:39,967
I can't wait to go home
with you.

9
00:00:40,033 --> 00:00:41,600
Before we go back to Manila,

10
00:00:41,667 --> 00:00:43,633
can we drop by
your family's place?

11
00:00:43,700 --> 00:00:45,167
I want to meet
your family.

12
00:00:45,233 --> 00:00:48,267
I'm sure I'm the last person
she wants to be there

13
00:00:48,333 --> 00:00:51,233
on the day she will introduce
her husband-to-be to her family.

14
00:00:51,300 --> 00:00:52,267
That's why I left.

15
00:00:53,400 --> 00:00:59,233
I'm happy for her because cuz
deserves that kind of man.

16
00:00:59,300 --> 00:01:05,767
Cuz deserves to catch
a bigger fish in the sea.

17
00:01:08,967 --> 00:01:10,500
Sorry, I forgot
that you're there.

18
00:01:10,567 --> 00:01:11,567
Sorry.

19
00:01:11,633 --> 00:01:14,267
We are not a perfect family.

20
00:01:14,333 --> 00:01:20,167
But what's important to us
is to see the two of you happy

21
00:01:20,233 --> 00:01:22,267
in the decision
that you will make.

22
00:01:22,333 --> 00:01:24,667
Sebastian, you should keep
your cellphone first.

23
00:01:24,733 --> 00:01:25,967
We're still eating.

24
00:01:26,033 --> 00:01:27,267
Sorry, Mother.

25
00:01:27,333 --> 00:01:29,133
My friend just texted me.

26
00:01:29,200 --> 00:01:30,800
Celeste went viral.

27
00:01:30,867 --> 00:01:32,233
You are a trending topic
right now.

28
00:01:33,267 --> 00:01:35,067
Do you know that
the Facepad App

29
00:01:35,133 --> 00:01:36,767
of the Municipal Hall is flooded
with negative comments?

30
00:01:36,833 --> 00:01:39,000
They're saying that
I'm not doing anything,

31
00:01:39,067 --> 00:01:43,200
that I just let the rich step on
the dignity of the Sorsoguenos.

32
00:01:43,300 --> 00:01:45,733
You know, Mayor, maybe
we shouldn't be impulsive

33
00:01:45,800 --> 00:01:46,733
with our decision.

34
00:01:46,800 --> 00:01:49,000
Once this issue dies down,

35
00:01:49,067 --> 00:01:50,900
I'm sure we can think
of something good to do.

36
00:01:50,967 --> 00:01:53,433
Maybe you're suggesting that

37
00:01:53,500 --> 00:01:56,000
because Celeste
is your former love?

38
00:01:56,067 --> 00:01:59,833
I think I have a brilliant
idea of how to deal with this.

39
00:02:03,733 --> 00:02:06,400
Famous fashion designer Celeste
is all over social media

40
00:02:06,467 --> 00:02:13,667
after a video of her damaging
a heritage site

41
00:02:13,733 --> 00:02:15,233
in the province
of Sorsogon was taken.

42
00:02:17,200 --> 00:02:19,600
The viral video has taken
a life of its own.

43
00:02:19,667 --> 00:02:22,167
Now the netizens are splicing
the dialogue

44
00:02:22,233 --> 00:02:23,733
and turning them
into dance music.

45
00:02:23,800 --> 00:02:25,567
This too will pass.

46
00:02:25,633 --> 00:02:27,100
Something else will come along

47
00:02:27,167 --> 00:02:30,733
and tomorrow, their attention
will no longer be on Celeste.

48
00:02:30,800 --> 00:02:33,200
Well, Sir, I agree with you.

49
00:02:33,267 --> 00:02:38,233
And usually, my advice is don't
mind or fight with the bashers.

50
00:02:38,300 --> 00:02:40,533
But Celeste,
what I'm worried about

51
00:02:40,600 --> 00:02:43,833
is the damage that
this is causing our brand.

52
00:02:43,900 --> 00:02:47,200
Maybe by the time
everything is over,

53
00:02:47,300 --> 00:02:50,833
the damage done to Celestial
is irreparable.

54
00:02:50,900 --> 00:02:54,600
The best course of action
right now is to go on camera

55
00:02:54,667 --> 00:02:56,967
and offer a public apology.

56
00:02:57,033 --> 00:02:59,833
Recognize the mistake
that you did.

57
00:02:59,900 --> 00:03:04,467
I'm not going on TV
because they will just mock me.

58
00:03:04,533 --> 00:03:08,067
And I'm not going to allow
myself to be put in a position

59
00:03:08,133 --> 00:03:10,433
where they will insult me.

60
00:03:10,500 --> 00:03:13,200
Celeste, you are being
unreasonable.

61
00:03:13,267 --> 00:03:14,767
I'm being unreasonable?

62
00:03:14,833 --> 00:03:16,267
I'm the victim here.

63
00:03:16,333 --> 00:03:17,833
They took a video of me.

64
00:03:17,900 --> 00:03:19,367
I can actually sue them.

65
00:03:19,433 --> 00:03:21,700
Because they took a video
of me and they released it

66
00:03:21,800 --> 00:03:23,167
without my consent.

67
00:03:23,233 --> 00:03:25,400
It's them who should
apologize, not me.

68
00:03:31,533 --> 00:03:32,533
Excuse me.

69
00:03:33,767 --> 00:03:34,900
Vivian?

70
00:03:34,967 --> 00:03:38,467
Tonito, have you seen
this video about Celeste?

71
00:03:38,533 --> 00:03:40,467
She is making a fool of herself.

72
00:03:40,533 --> 00:03:42,933
We are already trying to
address the situation, Vivian.

73
00:03:44,067 --> 00:03:45,367
Trying?

74
00:03:45,433 --> 00:03:47,467
What do you even
mean by that?

75
00:03:47,533 --> 00:03:49,867
Are you going to turn back time?

76
00:03:49,933 --> 00:03:52,533
Do you know the trouble
that woman brings?

77
00:03:52,600 --> 00:03:56,233
Tonight, I'll be hosting an
event for our investors.

78
00:03:56,333 --> 00:03:59,867
And she's going to ruin
that with her stupidity.

79
00:03:59,933 --> 00:04:01,567
They will talk about it.

80
00:04:01,633 --> 00:04:02,800
It's embarrassing.

81
00:04:02,867 --> 00:04:04,433
Vivian, please.

82
00:04:04,500 --> 00:04:06,500
Is she the one you plan
to marry, Tonito?

83
00:04:06,567 --> 00:04:09,667
She is an enemy
in the public eye.

84
00:04:09,733 --> 00:04:12,100
Do you think she will inspire
confidence

85
00:04:12,167 --> 00:04:15,633
in our business associates
the minute you marry her?

86
00:04:17,267 --> 00:04:20,433
I thought you are
intelligent, Tonito.

87
00:04:20,500 --> 00:04:24,633
And I was happy because
I thought someone will carry on

88
00:04:24,700 --> 00:04:27,033
what I've worked hard for.

89
00:04:27,100 --> 00:04:31,367
But I was wrong and I'm starting
to doubt myself...

90
00:04:31,467 --> 00:04:33,067
because clearly,

91
00:04:33,133 --> 00:04:38,033
my brother is capable of making
the worse decision of his life.

92
00:04:38,100 --> 00:04:42,433
The kind of decision that will
ruin him and what I've built.

93
00:04:47,033 --> 00:04:49,000
Guys, can you
give me a favor?

94
00:04:49,067 --> 00:04:50,400
I need to do this.

95
00:05:40,700 --> 00:05:45,000
Tonight our guest is a famous
fashion designer.

96
00:05:45,067 --> 00:05:48,267
That's the subject of a viral
video and the talk of the town

97
00:05:48,333 --> 00:05:50,167
on social media.

98
00:05:50,233 --> 00:05:51,433
Joining us via Zoom,

99
00:05:51,500 --> 00:05:53,333
it's Celeste of Celestial
fashion brand.

100
00:05:54,567 --> 00:05:56,967
Good evening, Celeste.

101
00:05:57,033 --> 00:05:59,567
Good evening, Ms. Ria.

102
00:05:59,633 --> 00:06:02,233
Are you still in Sorsogon?

103
00:06:02,300 --> 00:06:07,467
Yes. I'm here right now in my
father's house where I grew up.

104
00:06:07,567 --> 00:06:10,133
I'll be frank
with you, Celeste.

105
00:06:10,200 --> 00:06:13,133
What can you say
about the viral video...

106
00:06:14,200 --> 00:06:17,833
the netizens are angry about
right now?

107
00:06:17,900 --> 00:06:21,700
The truth is, I'm embarrassed
with what's happening,

108
00:06:21,767 --> 00:06:24,567
to the mistakes that I did.

109
00:06:24,633 --> 00:06:27,967
And most of all, I'm embarrassed
because I turned my back

110
00:06:28,033 --> 00:06:29,800
on my responsibilities.

111
00:06:31,367 --> 00:06:37,233
I was also shocked
when I saw the video.

112
00:06:37,300 --> 00:06:42,367
That's why, Ms. Ria, I ask
for forgiveness from all of you.

113
00:06:42,467 --> 00:06:43,767
To those who are watching

114
00:06:43,833 --> 00:06:47,833
and especially to
the townspeople of Sorsogon.

115
00:06:47,900 --> 00:06:49,800
I really made a mistake.

116
00:06:52,133 --> 00:06:57,200
To the bashers online
who said...

117
00:06:57,267 --> 00:06:58,900
that what I did was bad,

118
00:06:58,967 --> 00:07:02,967
I deserve and I accept that.

119
00:07:03,033 --> 00:07:08,533
I made a mistake
but I'll do everything to...

120
00:07:08,600 --> 00:07:13,133
correct the mistake
and face what I need to do.

121
00:07:13,200 --> 00:07:16,333
I hope that you can forgive me
and most of all,

122
00:07:16,433 --> 00:07:19,500
I hope I can forgive myself.

123
00:07:19,567 --> 00:07:23,100
So you're saying that the person
in the video

124
00:07:23,167 --> 00:07:27,833
is not the real Celeste
that we need to know?

125
00:07:27,900 --> 00:07:31,233
I don't want to come up
with any excuses.

126
00:07:31,300 --> 00:07:35,900
The truth is, I'm facing a lot.

127
00:07:35,967 --> 00:07:40,833
The stress, the pressure at work
and the people around me.

128
00:07:43,033 --> 00:07:46,300
That's why when I received
a call

129
00:07:46,367 --> 00:07:49,300
that my father
was brought to the hospital...

130
00:07:54,267 --> 00:07:55,433
sorry.

131
00:08:00,933 --> 00:08:01,933
I'm sorry.

132
00:08:03,033 --> 00:08:06,000
I rushed to come back here
in Sorsogon

133
00:08:06,067 --> 00:08:09,567
to see him in the hospital.

134
00:08:09,633 --> 00:08:12,800
That's why...

135
00:08:12,867 --> 00:08:16,967
I was not really
in the right frame of mind.

136
00:08:17,033 --> 00:08:20,000
Unfortunately...

137
00:08:20,067 --> 00:08:22,133
it was caught on camera.

138
00:08:25,433 --> 00:08:28,233
How is your father?

139
00:08:28,300 --> 00:08:30,533
He's okay now.

140
00:08:30,600 --> 00:08:34,233
What we are going through
is a bit hard.

141
00:08:34,300 --> 00:08:38,500
But I know as long as
we're together

142
00:08:38,567 --> 00:08:40,467
everything will be alright.

143
00:08:45,800 --> 00:08:49,667
Thank you so much.

144
00:08:52,933 --> 00:08:55,300
Don't worry, Bro.

145
00:08:55,400 --> 00:08:56,500
I'm still strong.

146
00:08:56,567 --> 00:08:58,900
I'm not going to die yet.

147
00:08:58,967 --> 00:09:02,100
You don't need to bring biscuits

148
00:09:02,167 --> 00:09:04,533
or have coffee here
in the house.

149
00:09:04,600 --> 00:09:05,900
Don't worry...

150
00:09:05,967 --> 00:09:07,733
when I die...

151
00:09:07,800 --> 00:09:10,100
you'll be the first one
I'll call

152
00:09:10,167 --> 00:09:12,767
so there will be gambling
in my wake.

153
00:09:15,100 --> 00:09:16,367
Father...

154
00:09:16,433 --> 00:09:17,867
you've been receiving
a lot of calls already.

155
00:09:17,933 --> 00:09:20,567
The next thing they'll ask you
is when you will die.

156
00:09:25,067 --> 00:09:26,533
Celeste, it's your fault.

157
00:09:26,600 --> 00:09:29,400
What did you say
to that Ria Campos?

158
00:09:29,500 --> 00:09:31,067
Why are you blaming me?

159
00:09:32,433 --> 00:09:34,000
Don't play innocent.

160
00:09:34,067 --> 00:09:38,567
You almost told the whole world
that father is going to die.

161
00:09:38,633 --> 00:09:41,200
I did not say that
father is going to die.

162
00:09:41,267 --> 00:09:42,600
And it's not my fault either

163
00:09:42,667 --> 00:09:44,867
if that's other people's
interpretation,

164
00:09:44,933 --> 00:09:47,233
like he is terminally ill.

165
00:09:47,300 --> 00:09:49,200
Okay, come on.

166
00:09:49,267 --> 00:09:51,400
Call Ria Campos.

167
00:09:51,467 --> 00:09:54,900
Have another interview and
correct what you've said.

168
00:09:54,967 --> 00:09:57,833
Tell her that father
is not going to die yet.

169
00:09:57,900 --> 00:09:59,367
Next time, make it clear.

170
00:10:01,000 --> 00:10:02,133
And do you think

171
00:10:02,233 --> 00:10:06,800
it's that easy to get
a primetime slot on the news?

172
00:10:06,867 --> 00:10:08,533
An interview?

173
00:10:08,600 --> 00:10:11,800
Don't you think that
I felt embarrassed?

174
00:10:11,867 --> 00:10:13,733
To look like a loser
and say all those things

175
00:10:13,800 --> 00:10:15,833
in front of the camera?

176
00:10:15,900 --> 00:10:19,867
Actually, why are you even
saying that I'm the liar?

177
00:10:19,933 --> 00:10:21,433
You're the liar.

178
00:10:21,500 --> 00:10:22,867
If you didn't make me haggard

179
00:10:22,933 --> 00:10:26,167
when you said that father
has an emergency, this and that.

180
00:10:26,233 --> 00:10:29,067
I shouldn't have gone all
the way here in Sorsogon.

181
00:10:29,133 --> 00:10:31,367
And I wouldn't have ended up
in this mess.

182
00:10:31,433 --> 00:10:35,133
So technically,
it's your fault.

183
00:10:35,233 --> 00:10:37,333
So this is actually
all your fault.

184
00:10:37,400 --> 00:10:41,633
Wow, you will really blame
everyone except yourself.

185
00:10:41,700 --> 00:10:43,200
Sebastian, that's enough.

186
00:10:43,267 --> 00:10:45,333
Go ahead, Mother.

187
00:10:45,400 --> 00:10:48,067
Side with that visitor.

188
00:10:48,133 --> 00:10:50,567
Tomorrow or the day after,
for sure she will leave again.

189
00:10:50,633 --> 00:10:51,600
Sebastian.

190
00:10:59,567 --> 00:11:01,267
Please be patient
with your brother.

191
00:11:05,933 --> 00:11:09,500
I'll talk to our friends

192
00:11:09,600 --> 00:11:11,833
who thought that
I'm going to die.

193
00:11:20,700 --> 00:11:22,267
Excuse me.

194
00:11:22,333 --> 00:11:23,033
Hello?

195
00:11:23,100 --> 00:11:24,200
Hello, Celeste.

196
00:11:24,267 --> 00:11:26,933
Oh my gosh, you're not
going to believe this.

197
00:11:27,000 --> 00:11:29,067
Can the bad news
be on another day?

198
00:11:29,133 --> 00:11:31,633
Can you just kinda fit
that in my schedule?

199
00:11:31,700 --> 00:11:33,533
What bad news are
you talking about?

200
00:11:33,600 --> 00:11:36,167
Dear, I am calling
because this is good news.

201
00:11:36,233 --> 00:11:39,733
All right, so I hired a company
to do social intel-listing.

202
00:11:39,800 --> 00:11:43,133
And guess what,
after your interview,

203
00:11:43,233 --> 00:11:46,600
the number of positive social
media engagement is growing.

204
00:11:46,667 --> 00:11:49,600
Celeste, many people
are sympathizing with you.

205
00:11:49,667 --> 00:11:50,667
Really?

206
00:11:50,733 --> 00:11:51,867
Yeah.

207
00:11:51,933 --> 00:11:55,800
Generally, people's opinion
is to stop judging you.

208
00:11:55,867 --> 00:11:58,200
They say that they can relate
to you.

209
00:11:58,267 --> 00:12:00,300
Because like an ordinary
person,

210
00:12:00,367 --> 00:12:03,200
you also experience ups
and downs.

211
00:12:03,267 --> 00:12:05,800
Not to mention that
they can relate to you

212
00:12:05,867 --> 00:12:08,433
because they know the struggle
of a daughter

213
00:12:08,500 --> 00:12:12,067
who is beside her parent while
he is slowly dying.

214
00:12:12,133 --> 00:12:14,100
You know, the only problem
Jamaica is

215
00:12:14,200 --> 00:12:16,467
that my father is not dying.

216
00:12:16,533 --> 00:12:20,600
Then that's good.
Who cares about what is true.

217
00:12:20,667 --> 00:12:22,933
Isn't it that in some posts,

218
00:12:23,000 --> 00:12:24,800
what's true is not the truth,
Celeste.

219
00:12:24,867 --> 00:12:27,467
The truth is what
the people believe.

220
00:12:27,533 --> 00:12:29,300
And what the people believe
right now

221
00:12:29,367 --> 00:12:31,800
is very good for our brand,
Celestial

222
00:12:31,867 --> 00:12:34,567
because many people
are sympathizing with you.

223
00:12:34,633 --> 00:12:36,367
As a matter of fact,
there's an increase

224
00:12:36,433 --> 00:12:39,133
in the engagement on our website
and electronic platforms.

225
00:12:39,200 --> 00:12:41,667
It looks like our sales will
increase in the next few days.

226
00:12:43,000 --> 00:12:46,933
And you remember that woman,
the one who gave harsh comments

227
00:12:47,000 --> 00:12:48,767
about your last collection?

228
00:12:48,867 --> 00:12:51,933
Oh my gosh dear, she tweeted.

229
00:12:52,000 --> 00:12:56,500
She said she was a bit harsh
in reviewing your collection.

230
00:12:56,567 --> 00:13:00,733
Now she understands why your
designs have dark undertones.

231
00:13:00,800 --> 00:13:03,800
It's because of the personal
things you are going through.

232
00:13:03,867 --> 00:13:06,833
And now she thinks
it's brilliant.

233
00:13:06,900 --> 00:13:09,700
Wow, really now?

234
00:13:09,767 --> 00:13:11,633
I guess that's good, right?

235
00:13:11,700 --> 00:13:13,367
I mean when everything is back
to normal

236
00:13:13,433 --> 00:13:16,767
then I can go back
to my life in Manila.

237
00:13:16,833 --> 00:13:18,933
Not so fast, Celeste.

238
00:13:19,000 --> 00:13:20,933
We have an opportunity here.

239
00:13:21,000 --> 00:13:22,633
We shouldn't let it go to waste.

240
00:13:23,767 --> 00:13:24,833
What do you mean?

241
00:14:04,867 --> 00:14:06,500
It looks like you had a long
conversation

242
00:14:06,567 --> 00:14:08,200
with your assistant.

243
00:14:11,700 --> 00:14:12,933
Yes, actually.

244
00:14:14,533 --> 00:14:16,033
We talked about
a lot of things.

245
00:14:16,100 --> 00:14:19,167
How we can move forward
from this situation.

246
00:14:19,233 --> 00:14:21,800
So the very first step
is to talk to the Mayor.

247
00:14:21,867 --> 00:14:24,500
Tell him we should start
with my community service.

248
00:14:24,567 --> 00:14:28,233
The faster the better
so everything will end.

249
00:14:28,333 --> 00:14:30,833
Hopefully, we can
document that also.

250
00:14:30,900 --> 00:14:34,233
It would be good while
I'm paying for my sins

251
00:14:34,300 --> 00:14:37,767
here in Sorsogon, I'm also
promoting my beloved province.

252
00:14:37,833 --> 00:14:41,067
And then after...

253
00:14:41,133 --> 00:14:42,867
hopefully,
that would clean my image.

254
00:14:42,933 --> 00:14:46,267
My PR Manager also said
all of it will be good for me.

255
00:14:46,333 --> 00:14:48,633
You know social media
is very big.

256
00:14:48,700 --> 00:14:49,967
There's a lot
of cancelled culture,

257
00:14:50,033 --> 00:14:51,167
there's a lot of people who
thought they knew everyting.

258
00:14:51,233 --> 00:14:54,600
So hopefully, I can un-cancel
myself with everything

259
00:14:54,667 --> 00:14:57,500
that I need to do
and really fix my image.

260
00:14:57,567 --> 00:14:58,700
Because at the end of the day,

261
00:14:58,767 --> 00:15:03,100
good image will bring money
for my business.

262
00:15:03,200 --> 00:15:04,800
That's good.

263
00:15:04,867 --> 00:15:08,000
That will help
your employees.

264
00:15:08,067 --> 00:15:09,133
How about me, Celeste?

265
00:15:09,200 --> 00:15:11,433
Can I help you
with something?

266
00:15:11,500 --> 00:15:16,900
Do you want to make it
look like me it's my wake?

267
00:15:16,967 --> 00:15:19,300
No need, that's fine.

268
00:15:19,367 --> 00:15:24,067
I just actually have to
stay here for a couple of days

269
00:15:24,133 --> 00:15:26,567
maybe weeks.

270
00:15:26,633 --> 00:15:28,733
You know, I have that
doting daughter image

271
00:15:28,800 --> 00:15:32,133
because it's not good
to see me staying in the hotel.

272
00:15:32,200 --> 00:15:35,400
So I just have to stay here
for a while.

273
00:15:35,500 --> 00:15:39,200
Why does it sound like
you're asking permission?

274
00:15:39,267 --> 00:15:40,667
You know...

275
00:15:40,733 --> 00:15:45,500
that you own
every corner of this house.

276
00:15:47,967 --> 00:15:49,900
This house is also yours,
Celeste.

277
00:15:54,567 --> 00:15:58,867
Let's not get overly
dramatic about that.

278
00:15:58,933 --> 00:16:02,033
Nothing less,
nothing more.

279
00:16:02,100 --> 00:16:03,067
You know, just think about it

280
00:16:03,133 --> 00:16:06,200
like it's a business
transaction.

281
00:16:06,267 --> 00:16:07,467
It has to be done.

282
00:16:07,533 --> 00:16:09,633
So I can...

283
00:16:09,733 --> 00:16:11,133
you know,
get out of here.

284
00:16:11,200 --> 00:16:12,967
Move on and continue
with my life.

285
00:16:13,033 --> 00:16:14,700
You can do the same.
Let's not meddle with each other

286
00:16:14,767 --> 00:16:17,667
just like before, okay?

287
00:16:17,733 --> 00:16:21,167
So I'm just going
to get my bag.

288
00:16:21,233 --> 00:16:22,367
Do you have an aircon here?

289
00:16:51,367 --> 00:16:56,167
Please allow me to introduce
our Provincial Tourism Head,

290
00:16:56,233 --> 00:16:59,867
mone other than,
Ms. Erlinda Escota.

291
00:17:04,433 --> 00:17:06,167
Good morning to you.

292
00:17:06,233 --> 00:17:07,967
Good morning.

293
00:17:10,000 --> 00:17:14,367
Ma'am Lyn, she is the famous
fashion designer

294
00:17:14,433 --> 00:17:17,200
and socialite that
we've been talking about.

295
00:17:17,300 --> 00:17:18,900
Miss Celeste.

296
00:17:21,733 --> 00:17:23,467
Is there something wrong?

297
00:17:23,533 --> 00:17:25,700
I just have something in my eye.

298
00:17:25,767 --> 00:17:28,167
Okay.

299
00:17:28,233 --> 00:17:31,033
See, I was right
with what I told you.

300
00:17:31,100 --> 00:17:36,033
She's like an angel who fell
on the ground, right?

301
00:17:36,100 --> 00:17:37,367
I totally agree.

302
00:17:37,433 --> 00:17:38,567
She is very beautiful.

303
00:17:38,633 --> 00:17:41,433
I saw your viral videos

304
00:17:41,500 --> 00:17:43,333
and you look very beautiful
in person.

305
00:17:44,767 --> 00:17:46,367
Thank you so much.

306
00:17:48,200 --> 00:17:52,000
Today is such a wonderful day.

307
00:17:52,067 --> 00:17:57,167
Because the daughter
of our town is here with us.

308
00:17:57,233 --> 00:18:03,200
Let's just say that Celeste made
a mistake the past few days.

309
00:18:05,267 --> 00:18:08,967
But like what I've said,

310
00:18:09,033 --> 00:18:11,600
even if you made a mistake
but if you're good,

311
00:18:11,667 --> 00:18:13,600
you can still stand up.

312
00:18:13,667 --> 00:18:19,267
And Celeste is here with us
making a sizeable donation

313
00:18:19,333 --> 00:18:21,300
for the heritage site
that she damaged.

314
00:18:21,400 --> 00:18:23,367
Wow.

315
00:18:23,433 --> 00:18:27,733
Not to mention,
rendering community service

316
00:18:27,800 --> 00:18:31,200
to make our town more beautiful.

317
00:18:31,267 --> 00:18:38,033
And Celeste will help us
in promoting Sorsogon

318
00:18:38,100 --> 00:18:41,000
through her social
media accounts.

319
00:18:41,067 --> 00:18:42,333
Do you know that...

320
00:18:42,400 --> 00:18:45,533
Celestial alone
has two million followers?

321
00:18:46,800 --> 00:18:51,367
It's two million followers while
the Mayor's Facebook account

322
00:18:51,433 --> 00:18:53,467
doesn't reach
one thousand likes.

323
00:18:54,867 --> 00:18:57,433
For sure, you're not liking
my posts.

324
00:18:57,500 --> 00:18:58,767
I'll check that later.

325
00:18:59,867 --> 00:19:03,500
Mayor, it's an honor
to be doing this

326
00:19:03,567 --> 00:19:05,600
with all of you here
in Sorsogon.

327
00:19:07,067 --> 00:19:11,700
To give me another chance
to correct my mistakes.

328
00:19:11,767 --> 00:19:13,433
Thank you so much.

329
00:19:13,500 --> 00:19:17,367
Like I said, I made a mistake
before and I really hope that

330
00:19:17,433 --> 00:19:24,133
I can live up to the ideals
of a true Sorsogueno.

331
00:19:24,200 --> 00:19:26,600
Again, thank you so much.

332
00:19:26,667 --> 00:19:28,633
May God bless us all.

333
00:19:28,733 --> 00:19:31,367
Every Sorsogueno
must help each other.

334
00:19:31,433 --> 00:19:34,100
- I love you all.
- Give her a round of applause.

335
00:19:34,167 --> 00:19:36,900
Let's take a selfie.

336
00:19:36,967 --> 00:19:38,433
I feel like I want
to have a selfie.

337
00:19:39,533 --> 00:19:41,933
Let's take a selfie.

338
00:19:42,000 --> 00:19:43,533
Join us, Ma'am Erlinda.

339
00:19:43,600 --> 00:19:45,333
Come here.

340
00:19:46,367 --> 00:19:47,667
Thank you.

341
00:19:49,000 --> 00:19:50,233
You're so cute.

342
00:19:50,300 --> 00:19:51,933
Let's give her another
round of applause.

343
00:20:05,533 --> 00:20:06,800
It's hot!

344
00:20:12,000 --> 00:20:13,633
What's this?

345
00:20:13,700 --> 00:20:14,767
Hassle.

346
00:20:17,267 --> 00:20:18,433
Wow, there's a signal.

347
00:20:18,500 --> 00:20:19,533
It's a miracle.

348
00:20:21,067 --> 00:20:22,867
Hello, Love?

349
00:20:22,933 --> 00:20:24,367
How are you?

350
00:20:24,433 --> 00:20:26,767
I'm okay.

351
00:20:26,833 --> 00:20:28,567
Well, I was actually
hesitant to leave you.

352
00:20:28,633 --> 00:20:31,000
But I guess my fears
were unfounded

353
00:20:31,067 --> 00:20:34,667
because I know that you can
handle everything.

354
00:20:34,733 --> 00:20:35,800
How is Vivian?

355
00:20:35,900 --> 00:20:37,867
Is she still
pissed off with me?

356
00:20:37,933 --> 00:20:40,567
Well, I haven't heard
anything from her.

357
00:20:40,633 --> 00:20:42,433
I guess she thinks that
this crisis

358
00:20:42,500 --> 00:20:43,900
is being handled brilliantly.

359
00:20:45,500 --> 00:20:46,933
What did I deserve

360
00:20:47,000 --> 00:20:50,100
to have a smart and charming
woman like you?

361
00:20:50,167 --> 00:20:52,433
You're sweet-talking again.

362
00:20:52,500 --> 00:20:55,933
What a pity,
my schedules piled up.

363
00:20:56,000 --> 00:20:58,100
Because I was enjoying
spending time

364
00:20:58,167 --> 00:21:00,733
with your family in Sorsogon.

365
00:21:00,800 --> 00:21:02,100
You know, Love, it's okay.

366
00:21:02,167 --> 00:21:05,200
You don't have to feel
obligated to be with my family.

367
00:21:05,267 --> 00:21:07,200
You've done enough.

368
00:21:07,267 --> 00:21:11,933
Well, the truth is, I just
can't wait to see you again.

369
00:21:12,033 --> 00:21:13,300
I know.

370
00:21:13,367 --> 00:21:14,967
Me too.

371
00:21:15,033 --> 00:21:16,333
I hate it here.
But you know what

372
00:21:16,400 --> 00:21:19,267
we have the rest of our lives
to be together.

373
00:21:19,333 --> 00:21:20,967
I know and I can't wait
for that.

374
00:21:26,600 --> 00:21:28,300
Love, I'll call you back.

375
00:21:28,367 --> 00:21:29,833
I love you.

376
00:21:29,900 --> 00:21:31,867
Okay, I love you too.

377
00:21:36,433 --> 00:21:39,033
Wow, how sweet.

378
00:21:39,100 --> 00:21:41,233
You were never that
romantic with me.

379
00:21:43,133 --> 00:21:44,900
I can't even remember
the last time

380
00:21:44,967 --> 00:21:47,533
you said I love you to me.

381
00:21:48,600 --> 00:21:49,600
Hello, Aurelia.

382
00:22:15,767 --> 00:22:18,233
Celeste, perfect, you're here.

383
00:22:18,300 --> 00:22:20,233
I will introduce you
to the coordinator

384
00:22:20,300 --> 00:22:22,333
for your community service.

385
00:22:22,400 --> 00:22:23,433
Who is it?

386
00:22:28,333 --> 00:22:30,300
You're wrong, Mayor.

387
00:22:30,367 --> 00:22:33,033
It's Celeste, not Celes-te.

388
00:23:15,800 --> 00:23:18,933
I asked Mikoy to report
about your community service.

389
00:23:19,000 --> 00:23:22,767
To be sure that you will take it
seriously, Celeste.

390
00:23:22,867 --> 00:23:24,300
I mean, Celeste.

391
00:23:26,733 --> 00:23:28,533
Is there no one else?

392
00:23:28,600 --> 00:23:30,633
I mean why him?

393
00:23:30,700 --> 00:23:33,100
Why? Do we have a problem
with that?

394
00:23:33,167 --> 00:23:38,233
Is it hard for the sweetness
of love to return...

395
00:23:38,300 --> 00:23:40,633
Mikoy?

396
00:23:40,700 --> 00:23:41,967
You're funny, Mayor.

397
00:23:44,033 --> 00:23:47,167
Mayor, believe me,
that past is past.

398
00:23:47,233 --> 00:23:48,900
What's important right now
is the present.

399
00:23:48,967 --> 00:23:51,667
I'll make sure that Celeste

400
00:23:51,733 --> 00:23:55,100
will fulfill her community
service arrangement.

401
00:23:55,200 --> 00:23:57,433
Unless you have plans
not fulfill

402
00:23:57,500 --> 00:23:59,833
so you can stay longer here

403
00:23:59,900 --> 00:24:01,767
that's why you keep
on complaining that it's me.

404
00:24:05,000 --> 00:24:07,300
Mayor, it's a good idea.

405
00:24:07,367 --> 00:24:09,033
- Yes.
- Aside from the fact

406
00:24:09,100 --> 00:24:11,433
that Mikoy and I
had a relationship before,

407
00:24:11,500 --> 00:24:13,767
everything will be easier.

408
00:24:13,833 --> 00:24:16,633
Thank you so much.

409
00:24:16,700 --> 00:24:17,767
You're welcome.

410
00:24:26,067 --> 00:24:28,300
You teased her.

411
00:24:28,400 --> 00:24:30,833
Of course, I had
to make a move.

412
00:24:49,333 --> 00:24:52,700
I'll stay here to help
our townspeople.

413
00:24:52,767 --> 00:24:54,600
So you're saying that
those who leave are bad

414
00:24:54,667 --> 00:24:56,400
because they have big dreams

415
00:24:56,467 --> 00:24:58,000
that they can't get here
in Sorsogon.

416
00:24:58,067 --> 00:24:59,300
Are you saying
they are selfish?

417
00:24:59,367 --> 00:25:01,000
I was impressed that she was
able to get out of the trouble

418
00:25:01,067 --> 00:25:02,100
she got herself into.

419
00:25:02,200 --> 00:25:04,300
You keep on underestimating her.

420
00:25:04,367 --> 00:25:06,400
Next time
she won't be that lucky.

421
00:25:06,467 --> 00:25:08,667
Join me for tea.

422
00:25:08,733 --> 00:25:11,200
Don't tell me you will avoid it.

423
00:25:11,267 --> 00:25:12,967
Is it true?

424
00:25:13,033 --> 00:25:14,267
Are you sure?

425
00:25:14,333 --> 00:25:17,567
This is still okay. We use this
when I cover fiesta.

426
00:25:17,633 --> 00:25:18,900
I cannot...

427
00:25:18,967 --> 00:25:22,300
I cannot appear in
a low-budget film.

428
00:25:22,367 --> 00:25:24,733
I'd rather use my phone
than that.

429
00:25:24,800 --> 00:25:26,000
This is high definition.

430
00:25:26,067 --> 00:25:29,533
Earlier, I was in a bad mood
because Celeste will stay here.

431
00:25:29,600 --> 00:25:33,700
But if because of her
every day is like a fiesta...

432
00:25:33,767 --> 00:25:35,500
she is very much welcome
with me.

433
00:25:35,600 --> 00:25:37,800
I genuinely love Tonito.

434
00:25:37,867 --> 00:25:40,633
And most of all,
he's not difficult to love.

435
00:25:40,700 --> 00:25:42,833
Mikoy, can you take a picture
of here later...

436
00:25:42,900 --> 00:25:45,667
for my OOTD?

437
00:25:45,733 --> 00:25:47,500
Anyway, it's beautiful.

438
00:25:47,567 --> 00:25:48,533
What will I do here?

439
00:25:52,733 --> 00:25:54,267
Nothing will happen
to you there.

440
00:25:54,333 --> 00:25:55,800
You should fix your position.

441
00:25:55,867 --> 00:25:58,167
You open it wide.

442
00:25:58,233 --> 00:25:59,967
- Like this.
- What?

443
00:26:00,033 --> 00:26:01,767
Everyone you've been
in a relationship with

444
00:26:01,833 --> 00:26:03,300
for the past two years,

445
00:26:03,367 --> 00:26:05,633
you're still looking
for dad in them.

446
00:26:05,700 --> 00:26:07,967
But I'm not saying this
to you to ridicule you

447
00:26:08,033 --> 00:26:11,033
or something but as a concerned
daughter,

448
00:26:11,133 --> 00:26:14,167
your happiness is
very important to me.

449
00:26:14,233 --> 00:26:17,767
Your Labella Figura
on your head is beautiful.

450
00:26:17,833 --> 00:26:19,067
It suits you.

451
00:26:19,133 --> 00:26:20,067
It suits you.

452
00:26:20,133 --> 00:26:21,767
The bag suits you.

453
00:26:21,833 --> 00:26:24,300
I feel dizzy.

454
00:26:24,367 --> 00:26:26,533
I'm getting annoyed.

455
00:26:26,600 --> 00:26:27,733
Ouch.

456
00:26:30,733 --> 00:26:32,867
I'll press it.

457
00:26:32,933 --> 00:26:42,900
Sorry.

458
00:26:47,900 --> 00:26:53,167
Sorry.
